@startuml
title Software Development Process Using CLI Coding Agents

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #F8F8F8
  BorderColor #555555
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF7E6
  DiamondBorderColor #555555
}
skinparam swimlane {
  BorderColor #555555
  TitleBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
  TitleFontStyle bold
}

|Researcher|
start

:Identify required functionality\nor system improvement;

if (Architecture decision required?\nnew package, library choice,\nmajor structural change) then (yes)
  :Evaluate architectural trade-offs mentally\n(impact on future work, library choices,\npackage structure);
  note right
  Inspired by ADR practice - decision is
  carefully reasoned but not formally
  documented; kept in the author's head.
  end note
  :Implement architectural step\nwith full author effort;
else (no)
endif

:Formulate idea with full technical context\n(task description, affected modules,\nexpected behaviour, constraints);

note right
  Key bottleneck: translating a precise,
  context-rich idea into a written prompt.
  Voice-to-text (local speech recognition)
  used to accelerate this step.
end note

:Write prompt — attach **@file** references\nfor relevant source files and provide\nadditional context where needed;

repeat

  |CLI Coding Agent\n(Claude Code / OpenAI Codex)|

  :Receive prompt and referenced file context;
  :Explore codebase\n(grep, ls, read files);
  :Plan implementation approach;
  :Implement requested functionality;
  :Write unit tests;
  :Execute shell commands\n(run tests, lint, verify output);
  :Return result — code changes,\ntest output, and summary;

  |Researcher|

  :Review generated code,\ntest results, and behaviour;

backward:Adjust prompt — correct\nmisunderstood requirements\nor add missing context;
repeat while (Result acceptable?) is (no)

:Accept and commit changes;

stop

legend right
  Developer time allocation in practice:
  majority spent crafting quality prompts
  and reviewing agent-produced results.
  Agents autonomously handle most steps
  of the implementation cycle.
endlegend

@enduml
